c6 3. Nf3 Nf6 4. e3 e6 5. Nbd2 c5 6. b3 b6 (6... Nc6 7. Bb2 cxd4 8. exd4 Ne4 9.
Bd3 Bb4 10. O-O Nxd2 11. Nxd2 dxc4 12. Nxc4 O-O 13. Be4 Ne7 14. Qd3 Ng6 15.
Rfd1 Rb8 16. d5 exd5 17. Qd4 f6 18. Ne3 Qa5 19. Qxd5+ Qxd5 20. Nxd5 Ba5 21. Bd4
{Karpov,A (2760)-Kaidanov,G (2640) Tilburg 1993 1/2-1/2 (48)}) 7. Bb2 Nbd7 8.
Bd3 $146 (8. cxd5 exd5 9. Bd3 Bb7 10. O-O Bd6 11. dxc5 Bxc5 12. Nd4 O-O 13. Nf5
g6 14. Nh6+ Kg7 15. Ng4 Kg8 16. Nxf6+ Nxf6 17. Nf3 Ne4 18. Rc1 Qe7 19. Nd4 Rac8
20. Qe2 Bd6 21. Nb5 Bb8 22. Ba3 Nc5 {Sherbakov,R (2580)-Beshukov,S (2435)
Krasnodar 1997 1-0 (48)}) 8... Bd6 9. O-O O-O 10. e4 dxe4 {Black forks: d3+f3}
(10... cxd4 11. cxd5 (11. Bxd4 $143 e5 $17) (11. Nxd4 Nc5 12. Bc2 Nfxe4 $11)
11... Nc5 12. Nc4 exd5 13. Nxd6 dxe4 14. Nxe4 (14. Nxc8 $2 {fails to} Nxd3 (
14... exd3 $6 15. b4 $11) (14... Rxc8 $6 15. Bxe4 Ncxe4 16. Nxd4 $11) 15. Qd2
Qxc8 (15... exf3 $143 16. Qxd3 fxg2 17. Rfc1 Rxc8 18. Qxd4 $17) 16. Nxd4 Rd8
$19) 14... Nfxe4 15. Bxe4 Nxe4 16. Nxd4 $11) 11. Nxe4 $14 Qc7 12. Nxd6 Qxd6 13.
dxc5 Qxc5 14. a4 Re8 15. Ba3 {White threatens to win material: Ba3xc5} Qc7 (
15... Qh5 $5 $14) 16. Bd6 $16 Qc6 (16... Qxd6 $4 {the bishop is invulnerable}
17. Bxh7+ $1 {Discovered attack: d3, Qd1xd6} Kxh7 18. Qxd6 $18) 17. Ne5 $4 {
weakening the position} (17. b4 $142 $16) 17... Nxe5 $15 (17... Qxd6 $4 {
Black will lose if he goes for the bishop} 18. Bxh7+ {Discovered attack: d3,
Qd1xd6} Kxh7 19. Qxd6 $18) 18. Bxe5 Bb7 {Black has a mate threat} 19. f3 $4 {
strolling merrily down the path to disaster} (19. Qf3 $142 Qxf3 20. gxf3 Bxf3
21. Rfe1 $15) 19... Ng4 {Black threatens to win material: Ng4xe5} (19... Qc5+
$142 {and Black can celebrate victory} 20. Rf2 Qxe5 $19) 20. Bd4 $4 {a transit
from better to worse} (20. Be4 $142 Qc5+ 21. Bd4 $14) 20... Rad8 $17 21. Be4 $4
{another step towards the grave} (21. c5 $142 bxc5 22. Bb5 $17) 21... Qc7 $19
22. Bxb7 (22. Bxh7+ {is one last hope} Kxh7 23. fxg4 $19) 22... Qxh2# 0-1

