11. Nd2 O-O 12. O-O-O Qd4 13. c3 Qc5 14. Kb1 b5 15. Be2 a5 16. Nb3 Qe7 17. h4
a4 18. Na1 {Zharkov,A (2251)-Smirnov,A (2404) Gornozavodsk 2007 0-1}) 4. Nc3
Be7 5. Bc4 (5. d4 exd4 6. Nxd4 O-O 7. Bc4 c6 8. O-O Re8 9. Re1 Bf8 10. Bb3 Nbd7
11. f3 Nc5 12. Bg5 Be7 13. Nce2 Nxb3 14. axb3 d5 15. e5 Nd7 16. Bxe7 Qxe7 17.
f4 {1/2-1/2 (17) Vincze,R (2187)-Fendrik,L (2198) Hungary 2007}) 5... O-O 6. d3
$146 (6. O-O c6 7. Bb3 b5 8. a3 a6 9. d3 Bb7 10. Kh1 Nbd7 11. Nh2 d5 12. exd5
cxd5 13. d4 exd4 14. Qxd4 Bc5 15. Qh4 d4 16. Ne2 Qb6 17. f3 Nd5 18. Rd1 d3 19.
Rxd3 Bf2 20. Qg5 Nc5 {Zelenika,D (2269)-Sertic,R (2330) Croatia 2005 0-1 (42)})
6... Nbd7 7. Be3 {Black has a cramped position. Black's piece can't move: c8}
Nb6 (7... c6 8. a4 $11) 8. Bb3 $14 Be6 9. O-O Bxb3 10. axb3 a6 {Prevents
intrusion on b5} 11. d4 Nbd7 12. d5 h6 13. Re1 Nh7 14. Ne2 f5 15. exf5 Rxf5 16.
Ng3 Rf7 17. c4 Ng5 18. Nxg5 (18. Nd2 $5 $16) 18... Bxg5 $11 19. Ne4 {The
knight feels good on e4} Bxe3 20. Rxe3 Nf6 21. Qd3 Qe7 22. Ng3 Raf8 23. Nf5 Qd7
24. Rg3 $4 {throwing away the advantage} (24. Ng3 $142 $11 {would save the game
}) 24... e4 $19 25. Nxh6+ Kh7 26. Nxf7 (26. Qc2 gxh6 27. Re1 $19) 26... exd3
27. Ng5+ Kg8 28. Ne6 Rf7 29. Rd1 (29. Rxd3 {hardly improves anything} c6 30.
Rad1 cxd5 31. cxd5 Qb5 $19) 29... Ne4 30. Re3 Nxf2 (30... Nc5 $142 $5 {keeps
an even firmer grip} 31. Nxc5 dxc5 32. Rdxd3 $19) 31. Rd2 Nxh3+ (31... c6 $142
{might be the shorter path} 32. Rxf2 Rxf2 33. Kxf2 cxd5 34. cxd5 Qc8 35. Rxd3
Qc2+ 36. Ke3 Qxg2 $19) 32. Rxh3 Rf6 (32... Qe7 33. Rdxd3 Qf6 34. Rd4 Qf2+ 35.
Kh2 Qxb2 36. Rg3 $19) 33. Re3 $2 (33. Rdxd3 $142 c6 34. Rd4 $15) 33... Qf7 $19
34. Rdxd3 (34. Re1 Qg6 35. Re3 Qf5 $19) 34... Rf1+ 35. Kh2 Qh5+ (35... Qf2 $142
{and Black can already relax} 36. Ng5 Qh4+ (36... Qxb2 $143 37. Re7 $19) 37.
Nh3 Re1 $19) 36. Rh3 $17 Qe5+ 37. Rhg3 Rf6 (37... Rf7 38. Rde3 Qf6 39. Ng5 $17)
38. Rde3 Qh5+ 39. Rh3 {White threatens to win material: Rh3xh5} Qd1 40. Ng5 (
40. Reg3 Rf7 $15) 40... Rf8 (40... Qf1 $142 41. Re8+ Rf8 $17) 41. Ne6 $4 {
with this move White loses his initiative} (41. Rh4 Qd2 42. Reh3 Qxg5 43. Rh8+
Kf7 44. Rf3+ Ke7 45. Rhxf8 Qh4+ 46. Kg1 Qd4+ 47. Kh1 Qh4+ 48. Kg1 Qd4+ 49. Kh1
Qh4+ 50. Kg1 $11) 41... Rf7 $4 {releasing the pressure on the opponent} (41...
Rf1 $142 {and Black is on the road to success} 42. Nxc7 Rh1+ 43. Kg3 Rxh3+ 44.
Kxh3 b5 $19) 42. Ng5 $11 {White has a mate threat} Rf8 43. Ne6 Rf7 $4 {Twofold
repetition. Black has let it slip away} (43... Rf1 $142 {a shame that Black
overlooked this excellent chance} 44. Rhf3 Rxf3 45. Rxf3 c6 46. Rf8+ Kh7 $19)
44. Ng5 $11 Rf8 1/2-1/2

