13. exd5 exd5 $17 (13... Nxd5 $143 14. bxc5 Bxc5 15. Nc3 $11)) 12. e5 $11 Nd7 {
Black threatens to win material: Nd7xe5} 13. cxd5 {White forks: c6+e6} Ncxe5 (
13... exd5 $5 {should be examined more closely} 14. Re1 c4 $11) 14. dxe6 $14 c4
$4 (14... fxe6 $142 {this is the best way to fight back} 15. Bc3 Nf7 $14) 15.
exd7 $18 Nxf3+ (15... Nxd7 {is no salvation} 16. dxc4 bxc4 17. Bxc4 $18) 16.
Qxf3 Bxd7 17. dxc4 Be6 (17... Bf6 {a fruitless try to alter the course of the
game} 18. Bc3 $18) 18. Rd1 (18. c5 {makes it even easier for White} Ra7 $18)
18... Rc8 (18... bxc4 {does not win a prize} 19. Bc3 Qc7 20. Nd2 $18) 19. Bg5
$1 {Discovered attack: d2, Rd1xd8} Qc7 (19... Bxg5 20. Rxd8 {Discovered attack}
) 20. Bxe7 Qxe7 21. c5 (21. Nd2 $142 {and White takes home the point} bxc4 22.
Qc3 $18) 21... Bxa2 22. Nc3 (22. h3 Be6 $18) 22... Bc4 (22... Bb3 23. Nd5 Bxd5
24. Qxd5 $16 (24. Rxd5 $4 Qe1+ 25. Rxe1 Rxe1#)) 23. Nd5 (23. h3 $142 $18) 23...
Be2 $4 {terrible, but what else could Black do to save the game?} (23... Bxd5
$142 24. Qxd5 Qf6 $16) 24. Nxe7+ $18 Rxe7 25. Qf4 (25. Qf5 $142 {seems even
better} Ree8 26. Rd7 Bc4 $18) 25... Bxd1 26. Rxd1 Rce8 (26... g6 {does not
help much} 27. h4 h5 28. Qf3 $18) 27. g3 Re4 28. Qc7 (28. Qxe4 Rc8 29. Qe7 h6
30. Rd8+ Rxd8 31. Qxd8+ Kh7 32. c6 h5 33. c7 f6 34. c8=Q Kg6 35. Qe8+ Kg5 36.
Qh3 h4 37. Qxh4+ Kf5 38. Qee4#) 28... R4e7 29. Qd6 (29. Qxe7 $1 g6 30. Qxe8+
Kg7 31. Rd7 Kf6 32. Qxf7+ Ke5 33. f3 h6 34. Rd5#) 29... Re6 $18 30. Qd3 (30.
Qd5 $142 {and White can already relax} a5 $18) 30... g6 (30... h5 {doesn't get
